POLIO - MEXICO (2)
===================

Last case of polio due to wild type virus in Mexico occurred on October
18th, 1990 in Tomatlan, state of Jalisco. Data from the General Direction
of Epidemiology, Ministry of Health.
Wild type poliovirus is considered eliminated from Mexico, since the 7th
of April, 1995.
The last isolation referred here was performed in the laboratory of
poliovirus, of our institute, by Dra. Oliva Clement head of the lab.
More details can be obtained from us.
--
